<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880210-0068 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Ryder System Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RDR </CO><IN> ERN </IN><TEXT>   Ryder System Inc. said 1987 net income rose 16% to $187.1 million, or $2.29 a share, from $160.9 million, or $2.09 a share, in 1986. Average shares outstanding totaled about 79.6 million, compared with 74.9 million in 1986.    Revenue increased 22% to $4.61 billion from $3.77 billion.    Profit for the Miami-based transportation and business services concern edged up 6.3% in the fourth quarter to $45.7 million, or 56 cents a share, from $43 million, or 55 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 20% to $1.22 billion from $1.02 billion. The 1986 quarter includes a $9.7 million gain from the sale of a unit.    Ryder cited strong growth in its core highway transportation services and aviation services operations. Pretax earnings from aviation services, for example, jumped 39% in 1987 to $59.9 million from $43 million in 1986.    In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday, Ryder's stock closed at $26.875 a share, unchanged. </TEXT></DOC>